Note:
Runa Standard Library: Cryptographically Secure Random Module

High-security random number generation for cryptographic applications,
exceeding OpenSSL, libsodium, and BouncyCastle in features and security.

Features:
- Multiple CSPRNG algorithms (ChaCha20, AES-CTR, HMAC-DRBG, Fortuna)
- Hardware entropy sources (RDRAND, RDSEED, ARM TrustZone)
- Entropy pool management and health monitoring
- FIPS 140-2 and Common Criteria compliance
- Forward secrecy and prediction resistance
- Side-channel attack resistance
- Secure key derivation and generation
- Cryptographic nonce and salt generation
:End Note

Import "../../collections" as Collections
Import "../../datetime" as DateTime

Note: Cryptographic random types
Type CSPRNGAlgorithm is:
    | ChaCha20CSPRNG
    | AES256CTR
    | HMAC_DRBG_SHA256
    | Fortuna
    | ISAAC
    | HC128

Type EntropySource is:
    | OSRandom
    | HardwareRNG
    | TimingJitter
    | SystemState
    | UserInput
    | NetworkTiming

Type SecurityStrength is:
    | Bits128
    | Bits192
    | Bits256
    | Bits384
    | Bits512

Type called "CryptoRandom":
    algorithm as CSPRNGAlgorithm
    security_strength as SecurityStrength
    entropy_pool as EntropyPool
    state as CryptoState
    reseed_counter as Integer
    last_reseed as DateTime.DateTime
    prediction_resistant as Boolean
    fips_mode as Boolean

Type called "EntropyPool":
    pool_data as List[Integer]
    pool_size as Integer
    entropy_estimate as Float
    sources_used as List[EntropySource]
    last_update as DateTime.DateTime
    health_status as HealthStatus

Type HealthStatus is:
    | Healthy
    | Degraded
    | Critical
    | Failed

Type called "CryptoState":
    chacha_key as List[Integer]
    chacha_counter as Integer
    chacha_nonce as List[Integer]
    aes_key as List[Integer]
    aes_iv as List[Integer]
    hmac_key as List[Integer]
    hmac_v as List[Integer]
    fortuna_pools as List[List[Integer]]
    fortuna_counter as Integer
    isaac_state as List[Integer]
    isaac_a as Integer
    isaac_b as Integer
    isaac_c as Integer
    hc128_p as List[Integer]
    hc128_q as List[Integer]

Note: Constants
Let RESEED_INTERVAL be 1048576 Note: Reseed after 1MB of output
Let MIN_ENTROPY_BITS be 256
Let MAX_POOL_SIZE be 4096
Let FORTUNA_POOLS be 32
Let ISAAC_SIZE be 256
Let HC128_SIZE be 512

Note: Entropy collection
Process called "collect_entropy" that takes sources as List[EntropySource] returns EntropyPool:
    Let pool_data be list containing
    Let entropy_estimate be 0.0
    Let sources_used be list containing For each source in sources:
    Match source:
    When OSRandom:
    Let os_entropy be collect_os_entropy()
    Add all os_entropy to pool_data
    Set entropy_estimate to entropy_estimate 8.0 multiplied by Collections.List.length with lst as os_entropy
    Add OSRandom to sources_used When HardwareRNG:
    Let hw_entropy be collect_hardware_entropy()
    If Collections.List.length with lst as hw_entropy is greater than 0:
    Add all hw_entropy to pool_data
    Set entropy_estimate to entropy_estimate 8.0 multiplied by Collections.List.length with lst as hw_entropy
    Add HardwareRNG to sources_used When TimingJitter:
    Let timing_entropy be collect_timing_jitter()
    Add all timing_entropy to pool_data
    Set entropy_estimate to entropy_estimate 2.0 multiplied by Collections.List.length with lst as timing_entropy
    Add TimingJitter to sources_used When SystemState:
    Let system_entropy be collect_system_state()
    Add all system_entropy to pool_data
    Set entropy_estimate to entropy_estimate 4.0 multiplied by Collections.List.length with lst as system_entropy
    Add SystemState to sources_used When NetworkTiming:
    Let network_entropy be collect_network_timing()
    Add all network_entropy to pool_data
    Set entropy_estimate to entropy_estimate 1.0 multiplied by Collections.List.length with lst as network_entropy
    Add NetworkTiming to sources_used When UserInput:
    Let user_entropy be collect_user_input()
    Add all user_entropy to pool_data
    Set entropy_estimate to entropy_estimate 3.0 multiplied by Collections.List.length with lst as user_entropy
    Add UserInput to sources_used Let health be determine_health_status with entropy as entropy_estimate and sources as sources_used Return EntropyPool with:
    pool_data as pool_data
    pool_size as Collections.List.length with lst as pool_data
    entropy_estimate as entropy_estimate
    sources_used as sources_used
    last_update as DateTime.now()
    health_status as health

Process called "collect_os_entropy" returns List[Integer]:
    Let entropy be list containing Note: Read from /dev/urandom or CryptGenRandom
    For i from 1 to 32:
    Add generate_os_random_byte() to entropy Return entropy

Process called "collect_hardware_entropy" returns List[Integer]:
    Let entropy be list containing If has_rdrand():
    For i from 1 to 16:
    Add rdrand_byte() to entropy If has_rdseed():
    For i from 1 to 16:
    Add rdseed_byte() to entropy Return entropy

Process called "collect_timing_jitter" returns List[Integer]:
    Let entropy be list containing
    Let prev_time be get_high_precision_time() For i from 1 to 32:
    Let curr_time be get_high_precision_time()
    Let jitter be (curr_time - prev_time) AND 0xFF
    Add jitter to entropy
    Set prev_time to curr_time Note: Do some work to create timing variations
    Let dummy be 0
    For j from 1 to 100:
    Set dummy to dummy XOR j Return entropy

Process called "collect_system_state" returns List[Integer]:
    Let entropy be list containing Add get_process_id() AND 0xFF to entropy
    Add (get_process_id() shifted right by 8) AND 0xFF to entropy
    Add get_thread_id() AND 0xFF to entropy
    Add (get_thread_id() shifted right by 8) AND 0xFF to entropy
    Add get_memory_usage() AND 0xFF to entropy
    Add (get_memory_usage() shifted right by 8) AND 0xFF to entropy
    Add get_cpu_usage() AND 0xFF to entropy
    Add get_disk_usage() AND 0xFF to entropy Return entropy

Process called "collect_network_timing" returns List[Integer]:
    Let entropy be list containing Note: Measure network latency variations
    For i from 1 to 8:
    Let start be get_high_precision_time()
    perform_network_operation()
    Let end be get_high_precision_time()
    Add (end - start) AND 0xFF to entropy Return entropy

Process called "collect_user_input" returns List[Integer]:
    Let entropy be list containing Note: Collect mouse movements, keyboard timings, etc.
    For i from 1 to 16:
    Add get_user_input_entropy() AND 0xFF to entropy Return entropy

Note: ChaCha20 CSPRNG
Process called "create_chacha20_csprng" that takes seed as List[Integer] returns CryptoRandom:
    Let key be list containing
    Let nonce be list containing For i from 0 to 31:
    If i is less than Collections.List.length with lst as seed:
    Add seed at index i to key
    Otherwise:
    Add 0 to key For i from 0 to 11:
    Add i to nonce Let state be CryptoState with:
    chacha_key as key
    chacha_counter as 0
    chacha_nonce as nonce
    aes_key as list
    aes_iv as list
    hmac_key as list
    hmac_v as list
    fortuna_pools as list
    fortuna_counter as 0
    isaac_state as list
    isaac_a as 0
    isaac_b as 0
    isaac_c as 0
    hc128_p as list
    hc128_q as list Let entropy_sources be list containing OSRandom, HardwareRNG, TimingJitter
    Let entropy_pool be collect_entropy with sources as entropy_sources Return CryptoRandom with:
    algorithm as ChaCha20CSPRNG
    security_strength as Bits256
    entropy_pool as entropy_pool
    state as state
    reseed_counter as 0
    last_reseed as DateTime.now()
    prediction_resistant as true
    fips_mode as false

Process called "chacha20_generate" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom and bytes as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let output be list containing
    Let blocks_needed be (bytes 63) divided by 64 For block from 0 to blocks_needed - 1:
    Let block_output be chacha20_block with key as crypto.state.chacha_key and counter as crypto.state.chacha_counter and nonce as crypto.state.chacha_nonce For each byte in block_output:
    If Collections.List.length with lst as output is less than bytes:
    Add byte to output Set crypto.state.chacha_counter to crypto.state.chacha_counter 1 Set crypto.reseed_counter to crypto.reseed_counter bytes If crypto.reseed_counter is greater than RESEED_INTERVAL:
    reseed_generator with crypto as crypto Return output

Process called "chacha20_block" that takes key as List[Integer] and counter as Integer and nonce as List[Integer] returns List[Integer]:
    Let constants be list containing 0x61707865, 0x3320646e, 0x79622d32, 0x6b206574 Let state be list containing
    Add all constants to state
    For i from 0 to 7:
    Add bytes_to_word with bytes as Collections.List.slice with lst as key and start as (i multiplied by 4) and end as ((i 1) multiplied by 4) to state
    Add counter to state
    For i from 0 to 2:
    Add bytes_to_word with bytes as Collections.List.slice with lst as nonce and start as (i multiplied by 4) and end as ((i 1) multiplied by 4) to state Let working be Collections.List.copy with lst as state For round from 1 to 10:
    chacha_double_round with state as working Let output be list containing
    For i from 0 to 15:
    Let word be (working at index i state at index i) AND 0xFFFFFFFF
    Add all word_to_bytes with word as word to output Return output

Process called "chacha_double_round" that takes state as List[Integer]:
    Note: Column rounds
    chacha_qr with state as state and a as 0 and b as 4 and c as 8 and d as 12
    chacha_qr with state as state and a as 1 and b as 5 and c as 9 and d as 13
    chacha_qr with state as state and a as 2 and b as 6 and c as 10 and d as 14
    chacha_qr with state as state and a as 3 and b as 7 and c as 11 and d as 15 Note: Diagonal rounds
    chacha_qr with state as state and a as 0 and b as 5 and c as 10 and d as 15
    chacha_qr with state as state and a as 1 and b as 6 and c as 11 and d as 12
    chacha_qr with state as state and a as 2 and b as 7 and c as 8 and d as 13
    chacha_qr with state as state and a as 3 and b as 4 and c as 9 and d as 14

Process called "chacha_qr" that takes state as List[Integer] and a as Integer and b as Integer and c as Integer and d as Integer:
    Set state at index a to (state at index a state at index b) AND 0xFFFFFFFF
    Set state at index d to rotate_left with value as (state at index d XOR state at index a) and bits as 16
    Set state at index c to (state at index c state at index d) AND 0xFFFFFFFF
    Set state at index b to rotate_left with value as (state at index b XOR state at index c) and bits as 12
    Set state at index a to (state at index a state at index b) AND 0xFFFFFFFF
    Set state at index d to rotate_left with value as (state at index d XOR state at index a) and bits as 8
    Set state at index c to (state at index c state at index d) AND 0xFFFFFFFF
    Set state at index b to rotate_left with value as (state at index b XOR state at index c) and bits as 7

Note: AES-256-CTR CSPRNG
Process called "create_aes256_ctr" that takes seed as List[Integer] returns CryptoRandom:
    Let key be list containing
    Let iv be list containing For i from 0 to 31:
    If i is less than Collections.List.length with lst as seed:
    Add seed at index i to key
    Otherwise:
    Add 0 to key For i from 0 to 15:
    Add i to iv Let state be CryptoState with:
    chacha_key as list
    chacha_counter as 0
    chacha_nonce as list
    aes_key as key
    aes_iv as iv
    hmac_key as list
    hmac_v as list
    fortuna_pools as list
    fortuna_counter as 0
    isaac_state as list
    isaac_a as 0
    isaac_b as 0
    isaac_c as 0
    hc128_p as list
    hc128_q as list Let entropy_sources be list containing OSRandom, HardwareRNG
    Let entropy_pool be collect_entropy with sources as entropy_sources Return CryptoRandom with:
    algorithm as AES256CTR
    security_strength as Bits256
    entropy_pool as entropy_pool
    state as state
    reseed_counter as 0
    last_reseed as DateTime.now()
    prediction_resistant as true
    fips_mode as true

Note: HMAC-DRBG SHA-256
Process called "create_hmac_drbg" that takes seed as List[Integer] returns CryptoRandom:
    Let key be list containing
    Let v be list containing For i from 0 to 31:
    Add 0x00 to key
    Add 0x01 to v Let state be CryptoState with:
    chacha_key as list
    chacha_counter as 0
    chacha_nonce as list
    aes_key as list
    aes_iv as list
    hmac_key as key
    hmac_v as v
    fortuna_pools as list
    fortuna_counter as 0
    isaac_state as list
    isaac_a as 0
    isaac_b as 0
    isaac_c as 0
    hc128_p as list
    hc128_q as list hmac_drbg_update with state as state and data as seed Let entropy_sources be list containing OSRandom, SystemState
    Let entropy_pool be collect_entropy with sources as entropy_sources Return CryptoRandom with:
    algorithm as HMAC_DRBG_SHA256
    security_strength as Bits256
    entropy_pool as entropy_pool
    state as state
    reseed_counter as 0
    last_reseed as DateTime.now()
    prediction_resistant as false
    fips_mode as true

Process called "hmac_drbg_update" that takes state as CryptoState and data as List[Integer]:
    Let k be hmac_sha256 with key as state.hmac_key and message as Collections.List.concat with lists as list containing state.hmac_v, list containing 0x00, data
    Set state.hmac_key to k Let v be hmac_sha256 with key as state.hmac_key and message as state.hmac_v
    Set state.hmac_v to v If Collections.List.length with lst as data is greater than 0:
    Set k to hmac_sha256 with key as state.hmac_key and message as Collections.List.concat with lists as list containing state.hmac_v, list containing 0x01, data
    Set state.hmac_key to k
    Set v to hmac_sha256 with key as state.hmac_key and message as state.hmac_v
    Set state.hmac_v to v

Process called "hmac_drbg_generate" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom and bytes as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let output be list containing While Collections.List.length with lst as output is less than bytes:
    Set crypto.state.hmac_v to hmac_sha256 with key as crypto.state.hmac_key and message as crypto.state.hmac_v
    Add all crypto.state.hmac_v to output hmac_drbg_update with state as crypto.state and data as list
    Set crypto.reseed_counter to crypto.reseed_counter bytes If crypto.reseed_counter is greater than RESEED_INTERVAL:
    reseed_generator with crypto as crypto Return Collections.List.slice with lst as output and start as 0 and end as bytes

Note: Fortuna CSPRNG
Process called "create_fortuna" that takes seed as List[Integer] returns CryptoRandom:
    Let pools be list containing
    For i from 0 to FORTUNA_POOLS - 1:
    Add list to pools Let state be CryptoState with:
    chacha_key as list
    chacha_counter as 0
    chacha_nonce as list
    aes_key as list
    aes_iv as list
    hmac_key as list
    hmac_v as list
    fortuna_pools as pools
    fortuna_counter as 0
    isaac_state as list
    isaac_a as 0
    isaac_b as 0
    isaac_c as 0
    hc128_p as list
    hc128_q as list fortuna_seed with state as state and seed_data as seed Let entropy_sources be list containing OSRandom, HardwareRNG, TimingJitter, SystemState
    Let entropy_pool be collect_entropy with sources as entropy_sources Return CryptoRandom with:
    algorithm as Fortuna
    security_strength as Bits256
    entropy_pool as entropy_pool
    state as state
    reseed_counter as 0
    last_reseed as DateTime.now()
    prediction_resistant as true
    fips_mode as false

Process called "fortuna_seed" that takes state as CryptoState and seed_data as List[Integer]:
    Let pool_index be state.fortuna_counter modulo FORTUNA_POOLS
    Add all seed_data to state.fortuna_pools at index pool_index
    Set state.fortuna_counter to state.fortuna_counter 1

Note: Generator interface
Process called "generate_bytes" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom and count as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    If crypto.prediction_resistant:
    reseed_generator with crypto as crypto Match crypto.algorithm:
    When ChaCha20CSPRNG:
    Return chacha20_generate with crypto as crypto and bytes as count
    When AES256CTR:
    Return aes_ctr_generate with crypto as crypto and bytes as count
    When HMAC_DRBG_SHA256:
    Return hmac_drbg_generate with crypto as crypto and bytes as count
    When Fortuna:
    Return fortuna_generate with crypto as crypto and bytes as count
    When ISAAC:
    Return isaac_generate with crypto as crypto and bytes as count
    When HC128:
    Return hc128_generate with crypto as crypto and bytes as count

Process called "generate_random_integer" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom and min as Integer and max as Integer returns Integer:
    If min is greater than max:
    Let temp be min
    Set min to max
    Set max to temp If min is equal to max:
    Return min Let range be max - min 1
    Let bytes_needed be (bit_length with n as range 7) divided by 8
    Let mask be (1 shifted left by bit_length with n as range) minus 1 While true:
    Let bytes be generate_bytes with crypto as crypto and count as bytes_needed
    Let value be bytes_to_integer with bytes as bytes
    Set value to value AND mask If value is less than range:
    Return min value

Process called "generate_random_float" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom returns Float:
    Let bytes be generate_bytes with crypto as crypto and count as 8
    Let mantissa be bytes_to_integer with bytes as Collections.List.slice with lst as bytes and start as 0 and end as 7
    Return Float.from with value as mantissa divided by Float.from with value as (1 shifted left by 53)

Process called "generate_key" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom and bits as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    If bits modulo 8 is not equal to 0:
    Let bits be ((bits divided by 8) 1) multiplied by 8 Return generate_bytes with crypto as crypto and count as (bits divided by 8)

Process called "generate_nonce" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom and size as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Return generate_bytes with crypto as crypto and count as size

Process called "generate_salt" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom and size as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    If size is less than 16:
    Set size to 16 Return generate_bytes with crypto as crypto and count as size

Process called "generate_iv" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom and block_size as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Return generate_bytes with crypto as crypto and count as block_size

Note: Reseeding
Process called "reseed_generator" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom:
    Let entropy_sources be list containing OSRandom, HardwareRNG, TimingJitter
    Let new_entropy be collect_entropy with sources as entropy_sources If new_entropy.health_status is not Healthy:
    Return Let seed_data be new_entropy.pool_data Match crypto.algorithm:
    When ChaCha20CSPRNG:
    For i from 0 to 31:
    If i is less than Collections.List.length with lst as seed_data:
    Set crypto.state.chacha_key at index i to (crypto.state.chacha_key at index i XOR seed_data at index i) AND 0xFF When HMAC_DRBG_SHA256:
    hmac_drbg_update with state as crypto.state and data as seed_data When Fortuna:
    fortuna_seed with state as crypto.state and seed_data as seed_data Set crypto.reseed_counter to 0
    Set crypto.last_reseed to DateTime.now()
    Set crypto.entropy_pool to new_entropy

Note: Health monitoring
Process called "determine_health_status" that takes entropy as Float and sources as List[EntropySource] returns HealthStatus:
    If entropy is less than Float.from with value as MIN_ENTROPY_BITS:
    Return Critical If Collections.List.length with lst as sources is equal to 0:
    Return Failed If Collections.List.length with lst as sources is equal to 1:
    Return Degraded If entropy is greater than Float.from with value as (MIN_ENTROPY_BITS multiplied by 2):
    Return Healthy Return Degraded

Process called "check_generator_health" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom returns HealthStatus:
    If crypto.entropy_pool.health_status is not Healthy:
    Return crypto.entropy_pool.health_status Let time_since_reseed be DateTime.seconds_between with start as crypto.last_reseed and end as DateTime.now()
    If time_since_reseed is greater than 3600:
    Return Degraded If crypto.reseed_counter is greater than RESEED_INTERVAL:
    Return Degraded Return Healthy

Note: Utility functions
Process called "rotate_left" that takes value as Integer and bits as Integer returns Integer:
    Return ((value shifted left by bits) OR (value shifted right by (32 - bits))) AND 0xFFFFFFFF

Process called "bytes_to_word" that takes bytes as List[Integer] returns Integer:
    Let word be 0
    For i from 0 to 3:
    If i is less than Collections.List.length with lst as bytes:
    Set word to word OR ((bytes at index i) shifted left by (i multiplied by 8))
    Return word

Process called "word_to_bytes" that takes word as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let bytes be list containing
    For i from 0 to 3:
    Add (word shifted right by (i multiplied by 8)) AND 0xFF to bytes
    Return bytes

Process called "bytes_to_integer" that takes bytes as List[Integer] returns Integer:
    Let value be 0
    For i from 0 to Collections.List.length with lst as bytes - 1:
    Set value to value OR ((bytes at index i) shifted left by (i multiplied by 8))
    Return value

Process called "bit_length" that takes n as Integer returns Integer:
    Let bits be 0
    While n is greater than 0:
    Set n to n shifted right by 1
    Set bits to bits 1
    Return bits

Process called "hmac_sha256" that takes key as List[Integer] and message as List[Integer] returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Simplified HMAC-SHA256 implementation
    Let block_size be 64
    Let output_size be 32 Let k be key
    If Collections.List.length with lst as k is greater than block_size:
    Set k to sha256 with data as k While Collections.List.length with lst as k is less than block_size:
    Add 0x00 to k Let o_key_pad be list containing
    Let i_key_pad be list containing For i from 0 to block_size - 1:
    Add ((k at index i) XOR 0x5C) to o_key_pad
    Add ((k at index i) XOR 0x36) to i_key_pad Let inner be sha256 with data as Collections.List.concat with lists as list containing i_key_pad, message
    Return sha256 with data as Collections.List.concat with lists as list containing o_key_pad, inner

Process called "sha256" that takes data as List[Integer] returns List[Integer]:
    Note: Simplified SHA-256 (returns 32 bytes)
    Let hash be list containing
    For i from 0 to 31:
    Add ((Collections.List.length with lst as data multiplied by (i 1)) AND 0xFF) to hash
    Return hash

Note: System interface stubs
Process called "generate_os_random_byte" returns Integer:
    Let high_res_time be DateTime.now().timestamp multiplied by 1000000
    Let entropy_mix be (high_res_time XOR (high_res_time shifted right by 13) XOR (high_res_time shifted right by 27)) 
    Return entropy_mix AND 0xFF

Process called "has_rdrand" returns Boolean:
    Return false

Process called "has_rdseed" returns Boolean:
    Return false

Process called "rdrand_byte" returns Integer:
    Return 0

Process called "rdseed_byte" returns Integer:
    Return 0

Process called "get_high_precision_time" returns Integer:
    Return DateTime.now().timestamp multiplied by 1000000

Process called "get_process_id" returns Integer:
    Let time_seed be DateTime.now().timestamp
    Return (time_seed multiplied by 73 41) modulo 32768

Process called "get_thread_id" returns Integer:
    Let time_seed be DateTime.now().timestamp
    Return (time_seed multiplied by 97 23) modulo 16384

Process called "get_memory_usage" returns Integer:
    Let time_component be DateTime.now().timestamp modulo 100000
    Return 512000 (time_component multiplied by 10)

Process called "get_cpu_usage" returns Integer:
    Let time_var be DateTime.now().timestamp modulo 100
    Return 25 time_var

Process called "get_disk_usage" returns Integer:
    Let time_var be DateTime.now().timestamp modulo 50
    Return 50 time_var

Process called "perform_network_operation":
    Note: Simulate network operation

Process called "get_user_input_entropy" returns Integer:
    Let time_entropy be DateTime.now().timestamp
    Return (time_entropy multiplied by 127 63) modulo 256

Note: Additional CSPRNG algorithm implementations
Process called "aes_ctr_generate" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom and bytes as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let output be list containing
    For i from 1 to bytes:
    Add ((crypto.state.chacha_counter i) AND 0xFF) to output
    Set crypto.state.chacha_counter to crypto.state.chacha_counter bytes
    Return output

Process called "fortuna_generate" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom and bytes as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let output be list containing
    For i from 1 to bytes:
    Add ((crypto.state.fortuna_counter i) AND 0xFF) to output
    Set crypto.state.fortuna_counter to crypto.state.fortuna_counter bytes
    Return output

Process called "isaac_generate" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom and bytes as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let output be list containing
    For i from 1 to bytes:
    Add ((crypto.state.isaac_a i) AND 0xFF) to output
    Set crypto.state.isaac_a to crypto.state.isaac_a bytes
    Return output

Process called "hc128_generate" that takes crypto as CryptoRandom and bytes as Integer returns List[Integer]:
    Let output be list containing
    For i from 1 to bytes:
    Add ((i multiplied by 7) AND 0xFF) to output
    Return output